id: pm-gygna8
title: pm deps tree must remain bounded on cyclic deep relationship graphs
description: "During full-lineage orientation, pm deps pm-kr3t --format tree --json expanded until the process exhausted roughly 4 GB of memory. Tree rendering needs cycle-safe visitation, explicit node/depth/token bounds, and a compact truncation diagnostic so graph context remains safe for agents."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags: []
created_at: "2026-07-23T11:25:44.855Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-23T11:26:20.051Z"
author: codex-root
acceptance_criteria: "Cyclic and multiply-linked graphs terminate without repeated unbounded expansion; Tree output honors explicit node, depth, and token bounds with deterministic truncation metadata; A regression fixture reproduces the deep richly-linked topology without touching the real tracker; CLI and SDK dependency projections retain parity for bounded results"
parent: pm-x85o
